Rating: 4
This was easy to make and so delicious. Made it as a side dish for Christmas dinner and it was a big hit with family. Comments received that it was light and refreshing. There was not enough dressing as the recipe calls for as it was a little dry, so I added another tablespoon and a half of fresh lime juice and oil. As per other cooks' suggestions, I added cumin, chili powder, and a sprinkle of dried basil. I also added a teaspoon or so of white sugar as I thought it was too tart. The coleslaw mix had carrots and purple cabbage to make it colorful. Will definitely make again.

