Rating: 4
I have loved this recipe since the first time I had it, many years ago, in Central America, where it is a popular dish. A twist to this recipe is to slightly wilt the coleslaw mix in boiling water before adding the dressing. This will make it easier on the digestive tract for those who react to cabbage's gas-producing qualities. The texture is, of course, slightly different, closer to some of the German-style slaws.

Rating: 4
I gave this 4 forks. I have made it multiple times now for various reasons. The ease of it for number one. An excellent dish without the typical mayo base. With the spice-rub chicken it was fab. I also LOVE cilantro and tended to use the whole bunch chopped in it. Guests have absolutely loved it as it was a new twist, great add in for fish or chicken tacos, and a wonderful, easy to prepare summer dish! Adding the salt to balance the acidity of the lime juice is also a must.

